# polka-dots agent instructions

## The one rule

`polka.toml` is the project entry point. `.polka` is the only built-in templating format.
Everything in `.polka/build/` is generated. If you edit generated output directly, your changes
will be lost on next build.

## Identity

polka-dots is a plugin-extensible dotfiles build engine. {{crate_count}} crates:

**SDK** (traits only ‚Äî what extensions depend on):
- `polka-primitives` ‚Äî `repr(C)` atoms, newtypes, base registration traits
- `polka-derive` ‚Äî proc macros (`#[register]`, `#[derive(Settings)]`)
- `polka-sdk` ‚Äî re-exports + domain trait contracts

**Core: Data** (host-side data management):
- `polka-data` ‚Äî file-backed data store, settings resolution, typed access
- `polka-catalogue` ‚Äî app/package/service catalogue (TOML registry files)
- `polka-project` ‚Äî project loading, single entry point

**Core: Execution** (host-side orchestration):
- `polka-pipeline` ‚Äî build/stage/deploy orchestration, manifest tracking
- `polka-scheduler` ‚Äî task scheduling, routine management
- `polka-audit` ‚Äî system audit against catalogue

**CLI:**
- `polka-cli` ‚Äî clap shell, I/O, output rendering, plugin loading

**First-party extensions** (cdylib, depend on SDK only):
- `polka-lang-polka` ‚Äî the `.polka` DSL (just a language plugin)
- `polka-source-brew` ‚Äî Homebrew/Cask/Tap source
- `polka-source-mas` ‚Äî Mac App Store source
- `polka-platform-macos` ‚Äî macOS platform
- `polka-platform-linux` ‚Äî Linux platform
- `polka-keybinds` ‚Äî keybind resolution

